                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 7.375,
                                "byte_start": 86859,
                                "byte_stop": 116430,
                                "text": "The second case is Robert O\u0027Neal v. Fred McAninch."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 7.375,
                                "stop": 29.535,
                                "byte_start": 116430,
                                "byte_stop": 205037,
                                "text": "This involves the following situation, a defended is convicted of a crime in a State Court, he comes into a Federal Habeas Court and he claims that there was a constitutional error that infected the trial for example of his conviction."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 29.535,
                                "stop": 40.695,
                                "byte_start": 205037,
                                "byte_stop": 249654,
                                "text": "The Court decides he is right, there was a constitutional error, but still he does not get a new trial if the matter was harmless."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 40.695,
                                "stop": 49.727,
                                "byte_start": 249654,
                                "byte_stop": 285808,
                                "text": "The question presented to us was under those circumstances who has to prove harmlessness or lack of harmlessness?"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 49.727,
                                "stop": 57.974,
                                "byte_start": 285808,
                                "byte_stop": 318826,
                                "text": "Is the burden on the defendant to show it was not harmless or is it on the government to show it was harmless?"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 57.974,
                                "stop": 66.947,
                                "byte_start": 318826,
                                "byte_stop": 354666,
                                "text": "What we decided is this, normally when you are a Court of Appeals or other court reviewing the transcript of a trial."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 66.947,
                                "stop": 71.22,
                                "byte_start": 354666,
                                "byte_stop": 371803,
                                "text": "The judge should try not to rely upon burdens of proof."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 71.22,
                                "stop": 76.933,
                                "byte_start": 371803,
                                "byte_stop": 394686,
                                "text": "The judge should read the transcript in the record and make up his or her own mind."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 76.933,
                                "stop": 91.039,
                                "byte_start": 394686,
                                "byte_stop": 451110,
                                "text": "In those rare instances where the judge ends up in grave doubt, then we think the burden is on the government to show that there was not harmlessness."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 91.039,
                                "stop": 97.629,
                                "byte_start": 451110,
                                "byte_stop": 477442,
                                "text": "That our reasoning that if that there was harmlessness that the burden is on the government, it shows that the error was harmless."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 97.629,
                                "stop": 109.685,
                                "byte_start": 477442,
                                "byte_stop": 525612,
                                "text": "A reason is basically it\u2019s consistent with prior president, it makes the law uniform and for reasons that we spell out in the opinion it is consistent with the interest of justice."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 109.685,
                                "stop": 115.722,
                                "byte_start": 525612,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Thomas has filed a dissenting opinion in which the Chief Justice and Justice Scalia have joined."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
